Key Match Events: Dane Myers hit a three-run homer and finished with a career-high five RBIs
Griffin Conine had three hits and an RBI
Nathan Lukes hit his first career home run
Miami Marlins won their third straight
Post-Match Reflections: Dane Myers said it was tough being on the sidelines while injured and he was happy to contribute
Skip Schumaker returned home to California because of a family medical issue and his bench coach Luis Urueta managed the team
Miscellaneous Highlights: Miami had been winless in its past eight series against Toronto, losing six and splitting two
The Blue Jays are 7-16 in September
Toronto slugger Vladimir Guerrero Jr. went 0 for 4 with a strikeout to remain one hit shy of 200
